HTTP Methods
Forms, Data Transferring, and Routing Rules

GET is used for passing insensitive information (show page)
POST is used for passing sensitive information. (sign in/up form)
PUT is used for passing updating whole sensitive information. (update page)
PATCH is used for passing updating pieces of sensitive information. (update)
DELETE is used for passing deleting sensitive information.

If your form data contains password data, credit card numbers, SSNs, etc, 
please use POST! If the information is something insensitive like a library search, 
it's OK to use GET as your method.